By my definition, this is not deep web. Zeronet is too mainstream to be considered deep web, imo.

If you ask if something is the deep web, then in all likelihood it is not. You'll know it if you see it. Tor is not by default deep web, but there are deep webs on tor if you catch my drift. Same goes with freenet and i2p.
